HW 28
_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Part A
Answer: C. 
Why: The most general class is a superclass. Since Snakes, Crocodiles, and Turtles are specific examples of reptiles, "Reptile" is a common parent class for all of them.
_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Part B
Answer: D.
Why: The method is asking specifically for a Guitar object. Although Acoustic and Electric are types of Guitar objects, an Instrument is not necessarily a Guitar object (it could be a drum or piano). You cannot pass a broader parent class into a method expecting a specific child class.